habitations. Yet he con&s;idered that his
<PB N="107" REF="111">
contempt was only the effect of his own &s;uperi|ority;
and that there might be &s;ome created be|ings
to whom his own &s;pecies mu&s;t appear as tri|fling.
His remark did not cea&s;e here. He con|&s;idered
