<P><PB N="232" REF="238">
IT may be prudent to give up the more trivial
parts of character for the amu&s;ement of the in|vidious:
As a man willingly relinqui&s;hes his &s;ilver
to &s;ave his gold from an highwayman. Better
be ridiculed for an untoward peruke, than be at|tacked
on the &s;core of morals, as one would
be rather pulled by the hair, than &s;tabbed to
