<P>VIRTUE &s;eems to be nothing more than a no|tion
con&s;onant to the &s;y&s;tem of things. Were a
planet to fly from it's orbit, it would repre&s;ent a
vitious man.</P>
<P>IT is difficult not to be angry at beings we
know incapable of acting otherwi&s;e than they
do. One ought no more, if one reflects, to be
