fancy happine&s;s in the paths which we
decline; and this heightens our unea&s;ine&s;s. We
might at lea&s;t e&s;cape the aggravation of it. It
is not improbable we had been more unhappy,
but extremely probable we had not been le&s;s &s;o,
had we made a different deci&s;ion. This, how|ever,
